@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

                       @{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}


This is an enhancement to BBSREAD arexx cmd @{"PackDataFile" link "BBSReadRexx.guide/packdatafile" 0}: before executing it
messages can be saved to disk with a @{i}nice@{ui} filename and a @{i}nice@{ui} header using
@{"GMarchive" link "GMarchive.guide/main" 0}! :-)

Selection is done by @{b}month@{ub} and @{b}year,@{ub} Unread or SuperUnread messages are never
processed.

The logic I've used is based on the KeepDays settings: if you have configured
a conference to keep only X days then it probably means you are not
interested in keeping an archived version too! :-)

Conference's KeepDays is used?

  Yes, only pack&purge the conference

  No, Global KeepDays is used?

      Yes, only pack&purge the conference

      No, save messages, delete them (note that messages marked @{i}Keep@{ui} are
          never deleted) and then pack&purge

At script end Event, User, Kill and File data are packed.


Please note that @{b}this script WILL DELETE messages@{ub} so please carefully check
the KeepDays configuration on your Thor!!! :-)


It is intended to be called from Thor Arexx script menu or from shell.

Of course it needs to be correctly @{"configured" link "Configuration" 0} before you can use it.
@endnode

@node "Configuration" "Creating a Configuration entry"

                  @{b}@{u}Configuring GMCleanConf@{ub}@{uu}


In ENV:Thor/ there must be a file called as @{b}system-name@{ub}_C.cfg, i.e. for a
System named @{b}Internet@{ub} a file @{b}ENV:Thor/Internet_C.cfg@{ub} must be created.

The '@{b}_C@{ub}' has to be used to avoid name duplication with GMSignature
configuration file (which ends with '@{b}_S@{ub}'). This means that a System name
@{u}should not be longer than 24 chars@{uu}!

When GMCleanConf is called, it gets both System and Conference names from
Thor then opens the .cfg file for the System and lookups for the Conference
tags. If a System is not currently open the script ends to avoid unwanted
runs! You must be inside the System you want to clean...

A DEFAULT tag is optional for this script.


The options are:

TAG  @{"pattern" link "Pattern" 0} string
     Keep        number      (optional, default @{i}zero@{ui})
     Path        string      (optional, default @{i}Thor Save Dir@{ui})


Which do the following; please note that if a string contains one or more
spaces it must be enclosed in quotes (@{b}"@{ub}) and optionals options can, of course
:-), be omitted.

TAG
    It must be the Conference name as configured within the system or, using
    the char @{b}*@{ub}, a Conference @{"pattern" link "Pattern" 0}.

Keep
    If the conference is an archive one with my @{"logic" link "Introduction" 0}, then set this to
    @{b}1@{ub} to not delete the messages found or set it to @{b}0@{ub} (or do not specify the
    keyword!) to delete them (note that messages marked @{i}Keep@{ui} are never
    deleted!)

Path
    Full path where msgs will be saved, default is "Thor Save Dir".
    Filename will be the Conference name with month & year as suffix


@{i}Sample configuration@{ui}

TAG   it.test
   Keep     1

TAG   Unwanted*
   Path        RAM:

TAG   default
   Path        Mail:MsgsSaved
@endnode

@node "Pattern" "Pattern"

             @{b}@{u}Using patterns as Conference name@{ub}@{uu}


To avoid typing multiple time the same signature for different Conferences
you can use a simple pattern matching.

The pattern char @{b}*@{ub} can be either in front, after or both.

When using tags with patterns is better to put them after normal tags to
avoid undesiderated matches! :-)

Sample configuration

TAG   it.test
   Keep        1

TAG   Unwanted*
   Path        RAM:

TAG   *ML
   Keep        1

TAG   *2hand*
   Path        Docs:Bargains


The second tag will be used for all the Conferences @{u}starting@{uu} with @{i}Unwanted@{ui},
the third for the ones @{u}ending@{uu} with @{i}(ML)@{ui} and the fourth for the ones that have
@{u}inside@{uu} @{i}2hand@{ui} (can be on start or end too!)
@endnode

@node "Thor" "Using with Thor"

                @{b}@{u}Using GMCleanConf from Thor@{ub}@{uu}


You may add it to the Arexx script menu or you may call it from shell.

The script accepts two parms: @{i}month@{ui} & @{i}year@{ui} to search. If not specified Thor's
RequestInteger function will be used to get these two values.

Unread or SuperUnread messages are never processed.

Using from shell can be easier and quicker, example from Thor's rexx
directory:

rx gmcleanconf.thor 10 1999

Validation is performed to the shell params:

 month >= 1    and <= 12
 year  >= 1978 and <= 2050
@endnode

